{"lemma":"نَذِيرٌ","slug":"نَذِيرٌ","root":"ن.ذ.ر","root_slug":"ن-ذ-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ن-ذ-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"نَذِير","root":"نذر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":58},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["name","noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n39622"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%86%D9%8E%D8%B0%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%B1%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"bringer of bad news, herald, legate, apostle, warner","examples":[{"text":"يَا أَيُّهَا النَّبِيُّ إِنَّا أَرْسَلْنَاكَ شَاهِدًا وَمُبَشِّرًا وَنَذِيرًا","english":"O Prophet, indeed We have sent you as a witness and a bringer of good tidings and a warner."},{"text":"هٰذَا نَذِيرٌ مِنَ ٱلنُّذُرِ ٱلْأُولَى","english":"This is a warner of the warners of old."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"messenger of God","tags":["broadly"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"warning","examples":[{"text":"نَذِيرُ شُؤْمٍ","english":"an ill omen"},{"text":"حِكْمَةٌ بَالِغَةٌ فَمَا تُغْنِ ٱلنُّذُرُ","english":"Extensive wisdom – but warning does not avail [them]."}]},{"pos":"name","gloss":"a male given name, Nadir"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/na.ðiːr/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n39622","headword_ar":"نَذِيرٌ","root":"n*r","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muno*irN","text_ar":"مُنْذِرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, M, A, Msb, K,) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"na*iyrapN","text_ar":"نَذِيرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M;) i. e. [One"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who gives information,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"advice, of a thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"things:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who warns;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who cautions;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and who puts in fear:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who gives notice to a people of an enemy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"other thing, that has come upon them;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a spy who gives notice, to a people, of an enemy, to put them on their guard;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A;) and in like manner ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"na*iyrapN","text_ar":"نَذِيرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a spy who informs an army of the state of the enemy:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, K:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"na*iyrN","text_ar":"نَذِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEiylN","text_ar":"فَعِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mufoEilN","text_ar":"مُفْعِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, L:) or its verb was"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"na*ara","text_ar":"نَذَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", but this has become obsolete: (T:) its pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nu*urN","text_ar":"نُذُرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, Msb, K;) occurring in the Kur, liv. 23, [&c.]. (TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Abw muno*irK","text_ar":"ابو مُنْذِرٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The cock"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har. p. 644). ―         -b3-  [And also,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~a*iyru","text_ar":"النَّذِيرُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The apostle:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) so in the Kur, xxxv. 34, accord. to Th: (M:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the prophet"},{"kind":"text","text":"Mohammad: (T, K:) so, accord. to most of the expositors, in that verse of the Kur. (T.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Hoariness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whiteness of the hair:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, K:) so, accord. to some, in the verse of the Kur, last referred to: (T, M:) but the explanation immediately preceding is more probable. (T.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The sound"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a bow: (AHn, M, K:) because it warns, or frightens, ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yunodiru","text_ar":"يُنْدِرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",) that which is shot at. (AHn, M.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mano*uwrN","text_ar":"مَنْذُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Vowed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nu*urN","text_ar":"نُذُرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"na*orN","text_ar":"نَذْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nu*orN","text_ar":"نُذْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["T","S","M","A","Msb","K","TA","L","AHn"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}